ZH: 我们将会一起渡过这段艰难时期。
EN: We will get through this difficult time together.

ZH: 他们正在渡过一条狭窄的河流。
EN: They are crossing a narrow river.

ZH: 她希望能够渡过考试。
EN: She hopes to pass the exam.

ZH: 我们需要一只船来渡过这个湖。
EN: We need a boat to cross this lake.

ZH: 春风无意渡江来。
EN: The spring breeze blows across the river.

ZH: 渡过百年不遂心。
EN: Living a hundred years without achieving ones desires.

ZH: 他渡过了曲折的一生。
EN: He went through a tortuous life.

ZH: 渡江，答山紋上浮。
EN: To cross the river; in answer to questions the mountain pattern is raised.

ZH: 流水渡来运舟难。
EN: It is difficult to ferry a boat on running water.

ZH: 此行必须渡过生死关。
EN: This trip must cross the life and death threshold.

ZH: 渡船在两岸之间往返。
EN: The ferry shuttles back and forth between the two banks.

ZH: 他渡过了这个疯狂的世界。
EN: He survived in this crazy world.

ZH: 渡边行者甚知风。
EN: A traveler who has crossed the border is fully aware of the winds.

ZH: 渡边人将我缘坚尽。
EN: Those living on the border will firm up my bonds.

ZH: 他们用长桨渡过这条河。
EN: They used long paddles to row across the river.

ZH: 渡船险过江，马过桥。
EN: The ferry is dangerous to cross the river, so the horse should cross the bridge.

ZH: 渡此即超然，满须用一生。
EN: Crossing this is transcendence and needs to be used throughout life.

ZH: 渡口吟诗谨入酒杯。
EN: At the ferry crossing, recite a poem and carefully drink the wine.

ZH: 雇佣人过渡江。
EN: Employ someone to ferry us across the river.

ZH: 我们需要渡过这片河流。
EN: We need to cross this river.
